              "text": "Contract: Four spades by South\nOpening lead: Spade five\n\nDraw trumps and knock out the ace of hearts. When back on lead, if no minor has been played, guess one and finesse into East, ensuring the contract. If you were to lead a minor before hearts, the defense might win the trick, cross to West with the ace of hearts, and lead the other minor."
